Class DeprecatedUCDWordList

  • java.lang.Object
    • ari.ucidy.UCDWordList
      • ari.ucidy.DeprecatedUCDWordList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<UCDWord>

    public class DeprecatedUCDWordList
extends UCDWordList
    Object listing and ordering alphabetically a set of deprecated UCD words.

    This class is an extension of UCDWordList. The only difference lies in the fact that to be added in this list a word MUST be deprecated, valid and recognised.

    Note: Words of this list may not have a UCD syntax code or a description.

    Since:
    1.1
    Version:
    1.2 (11/2021)
    Author:
    Grégory Mantelet (CDS)

        public int addAll(java.io.Reader reader,
                  boolean recommended)
           throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
                  java.io.IOException
        Add all deprecated UCD words declared inside the specified reader.

        The real parsing is performed by UCDParser.parseDeprecatedWordList(Reader, UCDWordList, DeprecatedUCDWordList). Please take a look to its Javadoc for more details about the expected syntax and the possible errors that can occur.

        Overrides:

        recommended - IGNORED in this implementation
